commitResults.messageTitle: Level 0. Renamed Chatbot and wrote skeletal version that prints a hello and goodbye message
Makes the program echo user inputs
Allows the building of a list storing data
Adds checkboxes to the list that can be marked and unmarked
Adds three types of tasks which each have their representation
Added semi-automated testing under text-ui-test
Added and catches every possible exception in the program
Added the delete command
Allow saving and loading tasks from hard drive
commitResults.messageBody:
Tasks are currently saved in an ArrayList, which disappears when the
program restarts.

Saving the tasks such that they are persistent will make the program
more useful and prevent data from being lost when the program quits.

Let's store the tasks in a text file in the data directory and update it
accordingly when the task list changes, and obtain tasks from it when
the program starts.

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge branch 'branch-Level-7'
Allow chatbot to understand dates and times
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, chatbot saved dates only as strings, which meant the user
could put in anything and it would have been accepted.

Saving dates as actual dates would allow better error checking and more
filtering functionality.

Let's save dates and print it out in a certain format, and add in a
search date function to demonstrate it's utility.

commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, the program was not as Object-Oriented.

In order to make the code more readable, the code will be split into the
4 files mentioned above, as well as Command objects.

So far, have implemented some methods in Ui, Parser, and Command.

commitResults.messageBody:
Previously could not search for tasks based on the task name.

Let's allow people to search for tasks by typing in a phrase that could
correspond to a part of the task name.
